Privacy Policy
WordWise: Dictionary & Games
Effective Date: April 22, 2026
Last Updated: April 22, 2026

1. Introduction
Welcome to WordWise: Dictionary & Games ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our mobile application ("App"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our practices.

By using the App, you agree to the terms described in this Privacy Policy.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 Information Stored Locally on Your Device
WordWise stores the following data only on your device and never transmits it to our servers:

Search History — Words you have searched for, stored locally for your convenience.
Favorites & Collections — Words you save or organize into collections.
Vocabulary Progress — Your learning progress, quiz scores, and flashcard results.
Game Stats — Wordle and Hangman game history and streaks.
App Preferences — Theme, notification settings, and other in-app settings.
You can delete all locally stored data at any time from Settings → Clear Data within the App, or by uninstalling the App.

2.2 Information Sent to Third-Party APIs
When you search for a word, the App sends the word query only (no personal information) to the following third-party dictionary services:

Free Dictionary API (dictionaryapi.dev) — to fetch word definitions, phonetics, and examples.
Datamuse API (datamuse.com) — to fetch synonyms, antonyms, and related words.
These services receive only the word you searched for. Please review their respective privacy policies for details on how they handle requests.

2.3 Advertising Data (Google AdMob)
The App uses Google AdMob to display banner advertisements. AdMob may collect and use the following information to serve ads:

Device identifiers (e.g., Android Advertising ID)
Device type, operating system version
General location (country/region level, not precise GPS)
App usage data and interaction with ads
This data is collected and processed by Google LLC under their own privacy policy. You can opt out of personalized ads via your device settings under Google → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization.

For more information, see Google's Privacy Policy.

3. Information We Do NOT Collect
We want to be clear about what we do not collect:

We do not collect your name, email address, or any account information.
We do not require you to create an account or log in.
We do not access your contacts, camera, microphone, or photos.
We do not track your precise GPS location.
We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties (beyond AdMob as described above).
We do not operate any servers that store your personal data.
4. Permissions Used
The App requests the following Android permissions:

Permission	Purpose
INTERNET	Fetch word definitions from dictionary APIs and load ads
ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE	Check network connectivity before making API calls
VIBRATE	Haptic feedback during games
POST_NOTIFICATIONS	Send Word of the Day daily notifications (optional)
RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED	Reschedule Word of the Day notifications after device restart
None of these permissions are used to collect personal information.

5. Text-to-Speech (TTS)
The App uses your device's built-in Android Text-to-Speech engine to pronounce words. This feature operates entirely on-device and does not send any audio data or text to external servers.

6. Children's Privacy
WordWise: Dictionary & Games is suitable for users of all ages, including children. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 years of age. Since the App does not collect personal data and requires no account registration, it is safe for use by children.

If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided personal information through the App, please contact us and we will promptly address the concern.

7. Data Security
All data generated by your use of the App is stored locally on your device using Android's secure Room database and DataStore. We do not operate external servers or databases containing your personal information, so there is no risk of server-side data breaches affecting your data.

8. Data Retention
Local app data (favorites, history, progress) is retained on your device until you clear it or uninstall the App.
Ad-related data collected by Google AdMob is subject to Google's own retention policy.
9. Your Rights and Choices
You have full control over your data:

Clear Search History — Settings → History → Clear All
Delete Favorites — Manage or delete any saved words at any time
Disable Notifications — Toggle off Word of the Day notifications in Settings or device notification settings
Opt out of personalized ads — Device Settings → Google → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization
Delete all data — Uninstall the App to remove all locally stored data
10. Third-Party Links
The App may display word definitions that include example sentences referencing external sources. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of any third-party websites or services.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically. Continued use of the App after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.

